text: Welcome to Chainlink Research Reports, a YouTube series featuring research across the web, three industry and academic fields with scholarship that expands our understanding of decentralized technologies. I'm Dr. Jason Anastasopoulos, a researcher at Chainlink Labs and an assistant professor of public policy and statistics at the University of Georgia. Today I'll be joined by Dr. Thomas Kerber, a technical architect at input output IOHK, who will be presenting his paper entitled Kashina Foundations of Private Smart Contracts. The paper provides a rigorous theoretical framework for privacy preserving smart contract design and implementation. Specifically, this paper proposes Kashina a protocol for deploying and securing privacy preserving smart contracts, which encompasses previous systems. Kerber then demonstrates how Kashina can be used to create a contract that implements privacy preserving payments along the lines of zcash, which is provably secure. And now here's Thomas Kerber.
